==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Selectman
<hw>Se*lect"man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Selectmen</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <def>One of a board of town
officers chosen annually in the New England States to transact the
general public business of the town, and have a kind of executive
authority. The number is usually from three to seven in each
town.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The system of delegated town action was then, perhaps, the same
which was defined in an ⟦ldquo⟧order made in 1635 by the inhabitants of
Charlestown at a full meeting for the government of the town, by
<qex>selectmen</qex>;⟦rdquo⟧ the name presently extended throughout New
England to municipal governors.</q> <rj><qau>Palfrey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Selectness</ent>⟦br⟧
